column1: #Text=Wikinews Interviews Australian wheelchair basketball player Georgia Inglis
#Text=Wikinews interviewed Georgia Inglis , of the Australia women 's national wheelchair basketball team , known as the Gliders .
#Text=The Gliders are in Bangkok , Thailand , for the Asia-Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships , which are being held at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center .
#Text=They are hoping to qualify for the World Championships , which are being held in Toronto , Canada , in June next year .
#Text=Inglis is one of two new players in the team .
#Text=Wikinews caught up with her before the Gliders ' match against China .
#Text=Georgia Inglis at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok , during the Asia-Oceania Zone Championships
#Text=According to the [ draft Wikipedia ] article , it says that you had an accident involving a ride-on lawn mower ?
#Text=The boy just did n't see me , so he ran over .
#Text=It says also that you were a tennis player and a swimmer .
#Text=Which sports did you get involved in ?
#Text=You were playing sports before your accident ?
#Text=I did tennis before my accident , and I did tennis after my accident and I did swimming after my accident .
#Text=And it says that you were a really good tennis player and swimmer .
#Text=I was a little bit competitive , but that 's about it .
#Text=So what made you take up basketball ?
#Text=I just enjoyed the team sport more .
#Text=Three or four years ago , I think it was .
#Text=A you joined the local team there ?
#Text=Then I trained with the Western Stars .
#Text=You 've been playing with them for three or four years .
#Text=And you were selected for the Osaka Cup earlier this year .
#Text=Which was your first overseas trip with the Gliders .
#Text=I saw you play in the [ WNWBL ] games .
#Text=You were particularly impressive in that final .
#Text=And so you were at a couple of training camps , and then you were selected for this .
#Text=Have you been overseas only to Toronto , or have you been elsewhere ?
#Text=No , I went to Italy and trained over there for three months .
#Text=well I did n't really play , but I trained with a team in Sardinia .
#Text=So you were part of the team ?
#Text=Yeah , but I did n't really play , just trained .
